            <p class="comment-content">Economic growth matters because growth improves the welfare of the majority of the population. It is not sufficient that growth benefits only a few elitist members of the society.  Many of the social problems in China today are a result of a malfunctioning economic process, and the right recipe to correct these problems is liberalization.</p>
        </div>
