      <li class="ctsh clearfix" data-cid="30187268">
        <div class="ilst">
          <a href="https://www.douban.com/people/mayback/"><img src="https://img3.doubanio.com/icon/u37252198-13.jpg" alt="弘毅" class="" /></a>
        </div>
        <div class="con">
          <div class="nlst">
            <h3>
              <div class="note-toggle rr">
                <a href="https://book.douban.com/annotation/30187268/" class="note-unfolder">展开</a>
                <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="note-folder">收起</a>
              </div>
              <a href="https://book.douban.com/annotation/30187268/" class="">第177页</a></h3>
          </div>
          <div class="clst">
            <p class="user"><a href="https://www.douban.com/people/mayback/" class=" " title="弘毅">弘毅</a>
              
                <span class="allstar50" title="力荐"></span>
            </p>
            <div class="reading-note" data-cid="30187268">
              <div class="short">
                
                  <span class="">Although it is true that Shanghai has had excellent GDP performance, much of this performance seems to have only moderately improved the living standards of the average Shanghainese.A huge portion of Shanghaiâ&euro;&trade;s GDP accrues not to Shanghaiâ&euro;&trade;s households as personal income but rather to the government in the form of taxes and to corporations in the form of profits......


Despite a rich history ...</span>
                  &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="https://book.douban.com/annotation/30187268/">(<span class="">3回应</span>)</a>
                <p class="pl">
                  <span class="">2014-01-16 23:10</span>
                  
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="all hidden" style="display:none" >
                Although it is true that Shanghai has had excellent GDP performance, much of this performance seems to have only moderately improved the living standards of the average Shanghainese.A huge portion of Shanghai’s GDP accrues not to Shanghai’s households as personal income but rather to the government in the form of taxes and to corporations in the form of profits......<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>Despite a rich history of business creation and risk-taking, entrepreneurship is almost completely missing in Shanghai today.<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>
                  <div class="col-rec-con clearfix">
                    







