              <div class="all hidden" style="display:none" >
                <blockquote><q>The era of Jiang Zemin was associated with an industrial policy and big-push government initiatives. The government of Hu Jintao reassigned policy priorities, now giving greater weight to social objectives. But, it is implementing those objectives via the heavy interventionism of the government. There is little recognition that many of the social problems in China today are a result of malfunctioning economic process, such as the blockage of small-scale entrepreneurship, and that the right recipe to correct these distortions is further liberalization.</q></blockquote>
